# Backend and Database Guidelines

## API Development
- Use Zod schemas to validate data exchanged with the backend
- Implement tRPC for type-safe API development between frontend and backend
- Follow tRPC best practices for router organization and procedure definitions

## Database Management
- Use Drizzle ORM for database schema management and type-safe database access
- Implement proper environment configuration for database access
- Follow separation of concerns in schema organization
- Keep database credentials, API keys, and other secrets secure and never commit them to the repository

## Testing and Quality Assurance
- Write unit and integration tests for critical components
- Use testing libraries compatible with React like vitest
- Ensure code coverage and quality metrics meet the project's requirements
- Run typecheck and lint commands locally before submitting code
- Follow the established patterns for testing components and utilities

## CI/CD and Code Quality
- Follow GitHub workflow for automated testing and linting
- Ensure all pull requests pass the CI pipeline before merging
- Use Turbo for caching to speed up CI/CD pipelines
- Maintain consistent code quality through automated linting and type checking
- Follow the pull request template for proper documentation of changes
